output.crosstab_text:
For Level 8 graduates of all subjects, 5 years after graduation, the industry with the highest proportion of female graduates is Administrative and support service activities, and the median earnings of females in this industry were £24,300. The industry with the highest proportion of male graduates was Wholesale and retail trade - repair of motor vehicles and motorcycles and the median earnings of males in this industry were £25,700.

The biggest difference in proportions is seen in Administrative and support service activities where the proportion of female graduates is 10.5 percentage points higher than the proportion of male graduates.

The biggest difference in median earnings is seen in Financial and insurance activities where the median earnings of female graduates were £4,600 higher than the median earnings of male graduates.

The group with the highest earnings was male graduates in the Transportation and storage industry (median earnings of £27,300).

7.2% of female graduates are concentrated in the top 2 industries (either Public administration and defence - compulsory social security or Education), whereas for male graduates this is 12.4%.
output.crosstab_title: Industry of graduate employment for graduates of all subjects by sex , 5 years after graduation, male and female Level 8 graduates from English HEIs, APs and FECs, 2018/19 tax year.
